---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="About — focused" description="The story behind focused, an AI note taker built for people who think while they talk." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article class="about">
				<header class="page-header">
					<h1>About focused</h1>
					<p class="subtitle">Built for people who think while they talk.</p>
				</header>

				<section class="prose">
					<h2>The problem we kept running into</h2>
					<p>
						It started in a product meeting. Someone said something important — a real insight — and by the
						time the meeting ended, nobody could quite remember how it was phrased. The notes captured the
						decision but lost the reasoning. The recording was there, but nobody had time to scrub through
						forty minutes of audio.
					</p>
					<p>
						That's the gap focused was built to close. Not just transcription, but comprehension. Not just
						a record, but a useful one.
					</p>

					<h2>What we believe</h2>
					<p>
						Note-taking is a tax on thinking. Every moment you spend writing is a moment you're not
						listening. And when you're not fully listening, you miss the nuance — the hesitation before an
						answer, the offhand comment that turns out to be the real issue, the idea that gets dropped
						because everyone moved on too quickly.
					</p>
					<p>
						We believe the best tools disappear into the background. focused is designed to be invisible
						during the conversation and indispensable after it.
					</p>

					<h2>Who we're building for</h2>
					<p>
						focused is for anyone whose work lives in conversation — founders running standups, consultants
						on client calls, researchers conducting interviews, managers in one-on-ones. People for whom
						the meeting is the work, not a distraction from it.
					</p>
					<p>
						Our early users told us the same thing over and over: they wanted to show up to meetings
						differently. Less anxious about capturing everything. More present. More useful to the people
						in the room with them.
					</p>

					<h2>Where we are now</h2>
					<p>
						focused is in early access. We're a small team working closely with a handful of users to make
						the product as useful as possible before we open it up more broadly. If that sounds like
						something you want in on, we'd love to hear from you.
					</p>

					<div class="cta-inline">
						<a href="/contact">Get in touch &rarr;</a>
					</div>
				</section>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
	}
	.page-header {
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
		padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray-light), 1);
	}
	.page-header h1 {
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
	}
	.subtitle {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.prose h2 {
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}
	.prose p {
		line-height: 1.75;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}
	.cta-inline {
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
	}
	.cta-inline a {
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 600;
		text-decoration: none;
	}
	.cta-inline a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
</style>
